  "text": "Property2: if the range R(x) is smaller than 5% or the number of users is small (n<25), then h(x) has more than one local minimum. In this case, if the range R(x) is small, then h(x) is a shallow function and its optimization does not provide a substantial gain. On the other hand, if n is small, then time complexity to check all n rotations is also small. These statistical properties of the function h(x) have been discovered by the author of this paper twenty four years ago via numerous computer experiments. Therefore, Property1 can be used to design a more elaborate algorithm that requires substantially less computation than the thorough parametric search over interval [CITATION_1] , [CITATION_2] .",
